-- With markets in chaos, G7 officials start meeting
-- 
-- Fri Oct 10, 2008 5:09pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/10/us-financial-g-7-meeting-idUSTRE4997P520081010

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - A meeting of finance ministers and central bankers of the Group of Seven major industrialized nations got under way at about 2:15 p.m. EDT (1815) on Friday at the U.S. Treasury Department. 

 Top economic officials are struggling to find ways to calm chaotic financial markets. (Reporting by  Mark Felsenthal ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)